4. 

# Partition (Training Dataset : Test Dataset = 7:3)
y      <- UB$Personal.Loan                            # Target
 
set.seed(200)
ind    <- createDataPartition(y, p = 0.7, list = T)   # Index  7:3 
UB.trd <- UB[ind$Resample1,]                          # Training Dataset
UB.ted <- UB[-ind$Resample1,]                         # Test Dataset

5.

Package "rpart" CART , CP (Complexity Parameter) . CP , CP . CP Cross Validation (CV) , Package 10-Fold CV . , Package "rpart" Package.

rpart(formula, data, method, ...)
  • formula : Target Target ~ .
  • data : formula (Data Frame)
  • method : Target "class", "anova" .
set.seed(200)                             # For CV
rContol      <- rpart.control(xval = 5)   # xval : xval-Fold CV
UB.trd.rtree <- rpart(Personal.Loan ~ ., data = UB.trd,                 
                      method = "class",   
                      control = rContol)         

summary(UB.trd.rtree)

Result! Table,

  • CP : Complexity Parameter Training Dataset . \[ \begin{align*} cp = \frac{p(\text{incorrect}_{l}) - p(\text{incorrect}_{l+1})}{n(\text{splits}_{l+1}) - n(\text{splits}_{l})}. \end{align*} \]
    • \(p(\text{incorrect}_{l})\) : Depth
    • \(n(\text{splits}_{l})\) : Depth
    • \(p(\text{incorrect}_{l+1})\) : Depth
    • \(n(\text{splits}_{l+1})\) : Depth
      , CP .

\[ cp = \frac{1.00-0.35}{2-0} = 0.325 \]

  • nsplit :
  • rel error : Depth Case ()
  • xerror : CV
  • xstd : xerror

7.

(Pruning) . Training Dataset . , , . Training Dataset Test Dataset . .
Package "rpart" CP . rpart() xerror CP .

table              <- UB.trd.rtree$cptable               # CP Table

low.error          <- which.min(table[ , "xerror"])      # min("xerror")  Index 
cp.best            <- table[low.error, "CP"]             # min("xerror")  CP (CP ) 

#  
UB.trd.prune.rtree <- prune(UB.trd.rtree, cp = cp.best)  # prune( , CP )

UB.trd.prune.rtree$cptable                               # Best  CP Table

1) Package pROC

pacman::p_load("pROC")

rtree.roc  <- roc(ac, pp, plot = T, col = "gray")      # roc( class,  )
auc        <- round(auc(rtree.roc), 3)
legend("bottomright", legend = auc, bty = "n")

Caution! Package "pROC" ROC .

#  plot.roc() 
plot.roc(rtree.roc,   
         col="gray",                                   # Line Color
         print.auc = TRUE,                             # AUC  
         print.auc.col = "red",                        # AUC  
         print.thres = TRUE,                           # Cutoff Value  
         print.thres.pch = 19,                         # Cutoff Value   
         print.thres.col = "red",                      # Cutoff Value   
         auc.polygon = TRUE,                           #     
         auc.polygon.col = "gray90")                   #    

#  ggroc() 
ggroc(rtree.roc) +
annotate(geom = "text", x = 0.9, y = 1.0,
label = paste("AUC = ", auc),

3) Package ROCR

pacman::p_load("ROCR")

rtree.pred <- prediction(pp, ac)                       # prediction( ,  class) 

rtree.perf <- performance(rtree.pred, "tpr", "fpr")    # performance(, "", "1-")                      
plot(rtree.perf, col = "gray")                         # ROC Curve

perf.auc   <- performance(rtree.pred, "auc")           # AUC
auc        <- attributes(perf.auc)$y.values
legend("bottomright", legend = auc, bty = "n")
